    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="The camp is located in the heart of the communities, in the middle of nowhere, and through its 10 tanks and a water treatment plant it is able to provide between 45,000 and 60,000 liters of water daily to the indigenous families of the area. Survival in Salta is very difficult, the temperature can reach 45º, the area is very arid and deserted. “Access to the communities is very complicated, there are no roads, we had to create them ourselves in order to be able to get there with our vehicles and bring water every two or three days. The children are waiting for us very excited, with the little cups ready… I have learned to value water very much, you realize how important it is when you don’t have it. Since we brought them the water, we have managed to reduce diarrhea and improve the children’s size, because before they took water from contaminated rivers, putting their health at risk."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 44 57 70 83 96 109 122 135 148 161 174 187 200 213 226 239 252 265 278 291 304 317 330 343 356 369 382 395 408 421 434 447 460 473 486 499 512 525 538 551 564 577 590 603 616 629 642 655 668 681 694 707 720 733 746 759 772 785 798 811 824 837 850 863 876 889 902 915 928 941 954 967 980 993 1006 1019 1032 1045 1058 1071 1084 1097 1110 1123 1136 1149 1162 1175 1188 1201 1214 1227 1240 1253 1266 1279 1292 1305 1318 1331 1344 1357 1370 1383 1396 1409 1422 1435 1448 1461 1474 1487 1500 1513 1526 1539 1552 1565 1578 1591 1604 1617 1630 1643 1656 1669 1682 1695 1708 1721 1734 1747 1760 1773 1786 1799 1812 1825 1838 1851 1864 1877 1890 1903 1916 1929 1942 1955 1968 1981 1994 2007 2020 2033 2046 2059 2072 2085 2098 2111 2124 2137 2150 2163 2176 2189 2202 2215 2228 2241 2254 2267 2280 2293 2306 2319 2332 2345 2358 2371 2384 2397 2410 2423 2428 2440 2445 2450 2455 2474 2493 2498 2503 2433 2479 2486 2460 2467 2508 2515 2522 2529 2525 2532 2536 2549"/>
